pageContext.description: Described and illustrated in the Archaeologia, as an object "not unlike the lid of jar, consisting of a convex circular plate with a shallow groove round margin + having attached to it and the concave side, a short tube of metal. Through this runs a hole for the Rivet bu which it was probably attached to a piece of wood". Cast marks show by Rivet holes. Single casting
pageContext.surface: Rough and corroded. Broken away round the edge and near one of the Rovet holes. Cast marks show by Rivet holes
pageContext.collection: Museum of Archaeology + Ethnology, Cambridge,Purchased by the Cambridge Antiquaries Society, April 1919,1919.b
pageContext.site: England,Cambridgeshire,Wilburton,In fen-land belonging to Mr. Oliver Claude Pell,1882
